by default.\\ndiff --git a/docs/exec-plans/active/007-mcp-initialize-and-tools-list.md b/docs/exec-plans/active/007-mcp-initialize-and-tools-list.md\\nindex 1d19b77..80d5d6e 100644\\n--- a/docs/exec-plans/active/007-mcp-initialize-and-tools-list.md\\n+++ b/docs/exec-plans/active/007-mcp-initialize-and-tools-list.md\\n@@ -5,7 +5,7 @@\\n   \\\"id\\\": \\\"mcp-initialize-and-tools-list\\\",\\n   \\\"title\\\": \\\"MCP Initialize and Tools List No-Auth Runtime\\\",\\n   \\\"order\\\": 7,\\n-  \\\"status\\\": \\\"queued\\\",\\n+  \\\"status\\\": \\\"active\\\",\\n   \\\"next_task_on_success\\\": \\\"mcp-tools-call-and-errors\\\",\\n   \\\"prompt_docs\\\": [\\n     \\\"AGENTS.md\\\",\\n@@ -102,3 +102,6 @@ Confirm that this task maps to the primary product spec `mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md\\n \\n - Start here. Append timestamped progress notes as work lands.\\n - Note when existing partial implementations were found and reused instead of replaced.\\n+- 2026-05-05T10:31:06.589Z: restored as current task after root-reset-defaults promotion.\\n+- 2026-05-05T10:33:14Z: found no existing MCP route implementation; reused the existing endpoint domain `generateMcpInputSchema` helper for tools/list rather than creating protocol-local schemas.\\n+- 2026-05-05T10:33:14Z: added stateless no-auth MCP handlers for `/mcp` and `/mcp/none`, documented MVP protocol/capability decisions, and added unit plus `@mcp-initialize-list` E2E coverage.\\ndiff --git a/docs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md b/docs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md\\nindex 303a47a..28ae238 100644\\n--- a/docs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md\\n+++ b/docs/product-specs/mcp-json-rpc-runtime.md\\n@@ -12,6 +12,16 @@ MCP connection guide examples\\n - Strict /mcp/none, /mcp/basic, /mcp/oauth routes\\n - Tool listing and calling\\n \\n+## No-Auth Initialize and Tool Listing\\n+- `/mcp` without `Authorization` and `/mcp/none` share the no-auth runtime path.\\n+- The MVP server supports JSON-RPC over Streamable HTTP `P